WEBVTT

00:00:29.300 --> 00:00:34.380
Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ, by the will of God,

00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:37.700
to the saints which are at Ephesus,

00:00:37.900 --> 00:00:40.540
and to the faithful in Christ Jesus.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.960
Grace be to you and peace from God our Father

00:00:44.960 --> 00:00:47.460
and from the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:52.020
Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ

00:00:52.020 --> 00:00:56.060
who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings

00:00:56.060 --> 00:00:58.960
in heavenly places in Christ,

00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:02.600
according as he hath chosen us in him

00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:05.080
before the foundation of the world,

00:01:05.400 --> 00:01:10.560
that we should be holy and without blame before him in love,

00:01:11.300 --> 00:01:17.240
having predestinated us unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:21.980
to himself according to the good pleasure of his will,

00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:31.300
to the praise of the glory of his grace wherein he hath made us accepted in the beloved,

00:01:31.980 --> 00:01:35.060
in whom we have redemption through his blood,

00:01:35.580 --> 00:01:39.960
the forgiveness of sins according to the riches of his grace,

00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:45.800
wherein he hath abounded toward us in all wisdom and prudence,

00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:50.180
having made known unto us the mystery of his will,

00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:55.020
according to his good pleasure which he hath purposed in himself,

00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:59.480
that in the dispensation of the fullness of times

00:01:59.480 --> 00:02:04.900
he might gather together in one all things in Christ,

00:02:05.320 --> 00:02:11.800
both which are in heaven and which are on earth, even in him,

00:02:12.580 --> 00:02:17.300
in whom also we have obtained an inheritance,

00:02:17.300 --> 00:02:21.740
being predestinated according to the purpose of him

00:02:21.740 --> 00:02:26.740
who worketh all things after the counsel of his own will,

00:02:27.160 --> 00:02:34.660
that we should be to the praise of his glory who first trusted in Christ,

00:02:35.020 --> 00:02:40.520
in whom ye also trusted after that ye heard the word of truth,

00:02:46.040 --> 00:02:49.860
ye were sealed with that Holy Spirit of promise,

00:02:50.100 --> 00:02:56.340
which is the earnest of our inheritance until the redemption of the purchased

00:02:57.420 --> 00:03:01.000
possession unto the praise of his glory,

00:03:01.380 --> 00:03:09.380
wherefore I also, after I heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus and love unto all the saints,

00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:15.200
cease not to give thanks for you, making mention of you in my prayers,

00:03:15.200 --> 00:03:20.340
that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of glory,

00:03:20.720 --> 00:03:28.080
may give unto you the spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him,

00:03:28.840 --> 00:03:34.260
the eyes of your understanding being enlightened that ye may know

00:03:34.260 --> 00:03:41.080
what is the hope of his calling and what the riches of the glory of his inheritance

00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:49.520
in the saints, and what is the exceeding greatness of his power to usward who believe

00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:57.080
according to the working of his mighty power which he wrought in Christ when he raised him

00:03:57.080 --> 00:04:04.660
from the dead and set him at his own right hand in the heavenly places far above all

00:04:08.560 --> 00:04:24.240
the world, and have put all things under his feet and gave him to be the head

00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:32.800
over all things to the church which is his body, the fullness of him that filleth all in all.

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:37.460
And you hath he quickened,

00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:45.740
which were dead in trespasses and sins, wherein in time past ye walked according to the course

00:04:45.740 --> 00:04:52.720
of this world according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit that now worketh

00:04:52.720 --> 00:05:00.760
in the children of disobedience, among whom also we all had our conversation in times past,

00:05:00.760 --> 00:05:08.100
in the lusts of our flesh, fulfilling the desires of the flesh and of the mind,

00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:18.780
and were by nature the children of wrath, even as others. But God, who is rich in mercy for his

00:05:18.780 --> 00:05:26.460
great love wherewith he loved us, even when we were dead in sins, hath quickened us together

00:05:26.460 --> 00:05:34.940
with Christ, by grace ye are saved, and hath raised us up together and made us to sit together

00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:43.920
in heavenly places in Christ Jesus, that in the ages to come he might show the exceeding riches

00:05:43.920 --> 00:05:52.360
of his grace in his kindness towards us through Christ Jesus. For by grace are ye saved through

00:05:52.360 --> 00:06:02.340
faith, and that not of yourselves, it is the gift of God, not of works lest any man should boast,

00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:11.600
for we are his workmanship, created in Christ Jesus unto good works, which God hath before ordained

00:06:11.600 --> 00:06:20.120
that we should walk in them. Wherefore remember that ye being in time past gentiles in the flesh

00:06:20.120 --> 00:06:29.500
who are called uncircumcision by that which is called the circumcision in the flesh made by hands,

00:06:30.740 --> 00:06:37.220
that at that time ye were without Christ being aliens from the commonwealth of Israel and

00:06:37.220 --> 00:06:45.840
strangers from the covenants of promise having no hope and without God in the world. But now in

00:06:45.840 --> 00:06:56.180
Christ Jesus ye who sometimes were far off are made nigh by the blood of Christ, for he is our

00:06:56.180 --> 00:07:03.280
peace who hath made both one and hath broken down the middle wall of partition between us,

00:07:03.800 --> 00:07:11.460
having abolished in his flesh the enmity even the law of commandments contained in ordinances

00:07:11.460 --> 00:07:21.080
for to make in himself of twain one new man so making peace, and that he might reconcile

00:07:21.080 --> 00:07:30.520
both unto God in one body by the cross having slain the enmity thereby, and came and preached

00:07:30.520 --> 00:07:40.700
peace to you which were afar off and to them that were nigh. For through him we both have access by

00:07:40.700 --> 00:07:49.900
one spirit unto the Father. Now therefore ye are no more strangers and foreigners but fellow citizens

00:07:49.900 --> 00:07:57.920
with the saints and of the household of God and are built upon the foundation of the apostles and

00:07:57.920 --> 00:08:06.960
prophets, Jesus Christ himself being the chief cornerstone in whom all the building fitly framed

00:08:06.960 --> 00:08:16.000
together groweth unto and holy temple in the Lord in whom ye also are builded together for

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:25.940
inhabitation of God through the Spirit. For this cause I, Paul, the prisoner of Jesus

00:08:25.940 --> 00:08:34.300
Christ, for you Gentiles, if ye have heard of the dispensation of the grace of God which is given me

00:08:34.880 --> 00:08:42.280
how that by revelation he made known unto me the mystery as I wrote afore in few words

00:08:43.180 --> 00:08:52.080
whereby when ye read ye may understand my knowledge in the mystery of Christ which in other ages was

00:08:52.080 --> 00:09:00.820
not made known unto the sons of men as it is now revealed unto his holy apostles and prophets by

00:09:00.820 --> 00:09:08.640
the Spirit that the Gentiles should be fellow heirs and of the same body and partakers of his

00:09:08.640 --> 00:09:17.220
promise in Christ by the gospel whereof I was made a minister according to the gift of the grace of

00:09:17.220 --> 00:09:26.760
God given unto me by the effectual working of his power unto me who am less than the least of all

00:09:27.180 --> 00:09:35.920
is this grace given that I should preach among the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Christ

00:09:36.280 --> 00:09:44.200
and to make all men see what is the fellowship of the mystery which from the beginning of the world

00:09:44.200 --> 00:09:53.500
have been hid in God who created all things by Jesus Christ to the intent that now unto the

00:09:54.020 --> 00:10:02.100
and powers in heavenly places might be known by the church the manifold wisdom of God

00:10:02.520 --> 00:10:09.960
according to the eternal purpose which he purposed in Christ Jesus our Lord in whom

00:10:09.960 --> 00:10:18.560
we have boldness and access with confidence by the faith of him wherefore I desire that ye faint not

00:10:18.560 --> 00:10:28.220
at my tribulations for you which is your glory for this cause I bow my knees unto the father of our

00:10:28.220 --> 00:10:37.120
Lord Jesus Christ of whom the whole family in heaven and earth is named that he would grant you

00:10:37.120 --> 00:10:44.100
according to the riches of his glory to be strengthened with might by his spirit in the

00:10:44.860 --> 00:10:51.720
that Christ may dwell in your hearts by faith that ye being rooted and grounded in love

00:10:51.720 --> 00:11:00.380
may be able to comprehend with all saints what is the breadth and length and depth and height

00:11:01.020 --> 00:11:14.080
and to know the love of Christ which passeth knowledge that ye might be filled with all the

00:11:14.080 --> 00:11:22.240
exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think according to the power that worketh in us

00:11:22.400 --> 00:11:34.600
unto him be glory in the church by Christ Jesus throughout all ages world without end amen end of

00:11:34.600 --> 00:11:36.940
one through three

00:12:03.720 --> 00:12:11.480
I, therefore, the prisoner of the Lord, beseech you, that ye walk worthy of the vocation wherewith

00:12:11.480 --> 00:12:18.640
ye are called, with all lowliness and meekness, with long suffering, forbearing one another

00:12:18.640 --> 00:12:24.800
in love, endeavouring to keep the unity of the spirit in the bond of peace.

00:12:25.540 --> 00:12:32.640
There is one body, and one spirit, even as ye are called, in one hope of your calling,

00:12:33.220 --> 00:12:42.560
one Lord, one faith, one baptism, one God and Father of all, who is above all, and through all,

00:12:42.880 --> 00:12:49.700
and in you all. But unto every one of us is given grace according to the measure of the gift of

00:12:49.700 --> 00:12:59.980
Christ. Wherefore, he saith, when he ascended up on high, he led captivity captive, and gave gifts unto

00:12:59.980 --> 00:13:08.480
men. Now, that he ascended, what is it but that he also descended first into the lower parts of the

00:13:08.480 --> 00:13:17.500
earth? He that descended is the same also that ascended up far above all heavens, that he might

00:13:17.500 --> 00:13:27.120
fill all things. And he gave some apostles, and some prophets, and some evangelists, and some

00:13:27.120 --> 00:13:33.560
pastors and teachers, for the perfecting of the saints for the work of the ministry, for the

00:13:33.560 --> 00:13:41.040
edifying of the body of Christ, till we all come in the unity of the faith, and of the knowledge of

00:13:41.040 --> 00:13:49.560
the Son of God, unto a perfect man, unto the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ,

00:13:49.980 --> 00:13:56.960
that we henceforth be no more children tossed to and fro, and carried about with every wind of

00:13:56.960 --> 00:14:04.400
doctrine, by the slight of men, and cunning craftiness, whereby they lie in wait to deceive.

00:14:04.400 --> 00:14:13.900
But speaking the truth in love, may grow up into him in all things, which is the head, even Christ,

00:14:14.780 --> 00:14:21.920
from whom the whole body fitly joined together and compacted by that which every joint supplyeth,

00:14:22.880 --> 00:14:29.540
according to the effectual working in the measure of every part, maketh increase of the body,

00:14:29.540 --> 00:14:36.420
unto the edifying of itself in love. This I say therefore, and testify in the Lord,

00:14:36.740 --> 00:14:45.280
that ye henceforth walk not as other Gentiles walk, in the vanity of their mind, having the

00:14:45.280 --> 00:14:52.500
understanding darkened, being alienated from the life of God through the ignorance that is in them,

00:14:52.500 --> 00:14:59.880
because of the blindness of their heart, who, being past feeling, have given themselves over

00:14:59.880 --> 00:15:07.940
to lasciviousness, to work all uncleanness with greediness, but ye have not so learned Christ.

00:15:08.680 --> 00:15:16.340
If so be that ye have heard him, and have been taught by him, as the truth is in Jesus,

00:15:16.340 --> 00:15:22.220
that ye put off concerning the former conversation, the old man, which is corrupt,

00:15:22.540 --> 00:15:30.220
according to the deceitful lusts, and be renewed in the spirit of your mind, and that ye put on

00:15:30.220 --> 00:15:37.520
the new man, which after God is created in righteousness and true holiness, wherefore putting

00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:45.360
away lying, speak every man truth with his neighbour, for we are members one of another.

00:15:46.360 --> 00:15:54.160
Be ye angry, and sin not, let not the sun go down upon your wrath, neither give place to the devil,

00:15:54.980 --> 00:16:01.640
let him that stole steal no more, but rather let him labour, working with his hands the thing which

00:16:01.640 --> 00:16:09.940
is good, that he may have to give to him that needeth. Let no corrupt communication proceed out

00:16:09.940 --> 00:16:17.600
of your mouth, but that which is good to the use of edifying, that it may minister grace unto the

00:16:17.600 --> 00:16:25.020
hearers, and grieve not the Holy Spirit of God, whereby ye are sealed unto the day of redemption.

00:16:25.780 --> 00:16:33.140
Let all bitterness and wrath and anger and clamour and evil speaking be put away from you,

00:16:33.140 --> 00:16:42.520
with all malice, and be ye kind one to another, tender-hearted, forgiving one another,

00:16:42.580 --> 00:16:45.680
even as God for Christ's sake hath forgiven you.

00:16:47.940 --> 00:16:57.480
Be ye therefore followers of God as dear children, and walk in love, as Christ also hath loved us,

00:16:57.480 --> 00:17:04.680
and hath given himself for us an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweet smelling savour.

00:17:05.500 --> 00:17:13.300
But fornication and all uncleanness or covetousness, let it not be once named among you,

00:17:13.820 --> 00:17:21.780
as becometh saints, neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting which are not convenient,

00:17:22.440 --> 00:17:30.960
but rather giving of thanks. For this ye know, that no whoremonger, nor unclean person, nor

00:17:30.960 --> 00:17:37.660
covetous man, who is an idolater, hath any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.

00:17:38.620 --> 00:17:45.040
Let no man deceive you with vain words, for because of these things cometh the wrath of God

00:17:45.040 --> 00:17:51.800
upon the children of disobedience. Be not ye therefore partakers with them, for ye were

00:17:51.800 --> 00:17:59.360
sometimes darkness, but now are ye light in the Lord. Walk as children of light, for the fruit

00:17:59.360 --> 00:18:06.640
of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth, proving what is acceptable unto the

00:18:06.640 --> 00:18:14.620
Lord. And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them.

00:18:15.040 --> 00:18:20.620
For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret.

00:18:21.600 --> 00:18:28.200
But all things that are reproved are made manifest by the light, for whatsoever doth

00:18:28.200 --> 00:18:36.000
make manifest is light. Wherefore he saith, Awake thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead,

00:18:36.640 --> 00:18:43.340
and Christ shall give thee light. See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools,

00:18:43.340 --> 00:18:51.840
but as wise, redeeming the time, because the days are evil. Wherefore be ye not unwise,

00:18:52.220 --> 00:18:59.420
but understanding what the will of the Lord is. And be not drunk with wine wherein is excess,

00:19:00.060 --> 00:19:06.780
but be filled with the Spirit, speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual

00:19:06.780 --> 00:19:14.980
songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord, giving thanks always for all things

00:19:14.980 --> 00:19:23.600
unto God, and the Father, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, submitting yourselves one to another

00:19:23.600 --> 00:19:31.800
in the fear of God. Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as unto the Lord.

00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:37.640
For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church,

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:45.340
and he is the saviour of the body. Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so let the

00:19:45.340 --> 00:19:52.860
wives be to their own husbands in every thing. Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also

00:19:52.860 --> 00:19:59.880
loved the church and gave himself for it, that he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of

00:19:59.880 --> 00:20:07.040
water by the word, that he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot

00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:16.740
or wrinkle or any such thing, but that it should be holy and without blemish. So ought men to love

00:20:16.740 --> 00:20:23.800
their wives as their own bodies. He that loveth his wife loveth himself, for no man ever yet hated

00:20:23.800 --> 00:20:32.800
his own flesh, but nourisheth and cherisheth it, even as the Lord the church. For we are members

00:20:32.800 --> 00:20:40.940
of his body, of his flesh, and of his bones. For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother,

00:20:41.320 --> 00:20:48.360
and shall be joined unto his wife, and they too shall be one flesh. This is a great mystery,

00:20:48.360 --> 00:20:55.420
but I speak concerning Christ and the church. Nevertheless, let every one of you in particular

00:20:55.420 --> 00:21:02.420
so love his wife even as himself, and the wife see that she reverence her husband.

00:21:04.000 --> 00:21:11.700
Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right. Honour thy father and mother,

00:21:11.700 --> 00:21:19.480
which is the first commandment with promise, that it may be well with thee, and thou mayest

00:21:19.480 --> 00:21:27.020
live long on the earth. And ye fathers, provoke not your children to wrath, but bring them up

00:21:27.020 --> 00:21:34.940
in the nurture and admonition of the Lord. Servants, be obedient to them that are your

00:21:34.940 --> 00:21:40.780
masters according to the flesh, with fear and trembling, and singleness of your heart,

00:21:40.780 --> 00:21:47.740
as unto Christ, not with eye-service, as men-pleasers, but as the servants of Christ,

00:21:48.160 --> 00:21:54.800
doing the will of God from the heart, with goodwill doing service, as to the Lord and not to men,

00:21:55.300 --> 00:22:00.520
knowing that whatsoever good thing any man doeth, the same shall he receive of the Lord,

00:22:00.740 --> 00:22:07.940
whether he be bond or free. And ye masters, do the same things unto them, forbearing threatening,

00:22:07.940 --> 00:22:14.040
knowing that your master also is in heaven, neither is there respect of persons with him.

00:22:14.460 --> 00:22:19.940
Finally, my brethren, be strong in the Lord, and in the power of his might.

00:22:20.900 --> 00:22:28.060
Put on the whole armour of God, that ye may be able to stand against the wiles of the devil.

00:22:28.600 --> 00:22:35.020
For we wrestle not against flesh and blood, but against principalities, against powers,

00:22:35.020 --> 00:22:42.060
against the rulers of the darkness of this world, against spiritual wickedness in high places.

00:22:43.180 --> 00:22:48.720
Wherefore, take unto you the whole armour of God, that ye may be able to withstand

00:22:49.260 --> 00:22:57.780
in the evil day, and having done all, to stand. Stand therefore, having your loins girt about

00:22:57.780 --> 00:23:04.040
with truth, and having on the breastplate of righteousness, and your feet shod with the

00:23:04.040 --> 00:23:11.100
preparation of the gospel of peace. Above all, taking the shield of faith, wherewith ye shall

00:23:11.100 --> 00:23:17.440
be able to quench all the fiery darts of the wicked. And take the helmet of salvation,

00:23:17.920 --> 00:23:23.600
and the sword of the spirit, which is the word of God. Praying always with all prayer,

00:23:23.980 --> 00:23:30.300
and supplication in the spirit, and watching thereunto with all perseverance, and supplication

00:23:30.300 --> 00:23:38.700
for all saints. And for me, that utterance may be given unto me, that I may open my mouth boldly,

00:23:39.620 --> 00:23:46.080
to make known the mystery of the gospel, for which I am an ambassador in bonds, that therein

00:23:46.080 --> 00:23:53.140
I may speak boldly, as I ought to speak. But that ye also may know my affairs, and how I do,

00:23:53.340 --> 00:23:59.500
Tychicus, a beloved brother and faithful minister in the Lord, shall make known to you all things,

00:23:59.500 --> 00:24:06.360
whom I have sent unto you for the same purpose, that ye might know our affairs,

00:24:06.760 --> 00:24:14.520
and that ye might comfort your hearts. Peace be to the brethren, and love with faith from God the

00:24:14.520 --> 00:24:23.600
Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ. Grace be with all them that love our Lord Jesus Christ in sincerity.

00:24:23.600 --> 00:24:25.320
Amen.
